cell("markdown","---\n## Phase 3 — Olympiad Extension\n\n### Challenge: Matrix Power $A^n$ in $O(\\log n)$ Time\nComputing $A^{10}$ as $A \\times A \\dots \\times A$ takes 9 multiplications.\nYou can do it in 4 multiplications using **Exponentiation by Squaring**:\n$A^2 = A \\times A$\n$A^4 = A^2 \\times A^2$\n$A^8 = A^4 \\times A^4$\n$A^{10} = A^8 \\times A^2$\n\nImplement `power(self, n)` using this algorithm."),
