cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\nExplain why calculating the determinant via RREF takes $O(N^3)$ time, whereas recursive cofactor expansion takes $O(N!)$ time. What are the two nested loops occurring inside the `while` loop of RREF?\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\nThe while loop runs $N$ times. Inside, we find a pivot ($O(N)$), and then we eliminate all other rows by subtracting a multiple of the pivot row. Subtracting a row from another row requires iterating over all $N$ columns. Doing this for $N$ rows takes $N \\times N = O(N^2)$ time inside the while loop. \nTotal time: $N \\times O(N^2) = O(N^3)$.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Algorithms 16 (K-Means Clustering)")
