cell("markdown","---\n## Phase 1 — Algorithm Construction\n\n### Step 1: Initialization\nWrite a function to randomly assign initial cluster labels to $N$ data points. Ensure every cluster $0$ to $K-1$ gets at least one point! (e.g. count off 0, 1, 2, 0, 1, 2, then shuffle)."),
cell("code","import random\ndef initialize_clusters(data, k):\n    '''Return a list of initial cluster labels (integers 0 to k-1) for each data point.'''\n    # YOUR CODE HERE\n    pass"),
cell("markdown","### Step 2: The K-Means Loop\nPut the initialization, assignment, and update steps together. Loop until the labels array doesn't change from the previous iteration."),
cell("code","def kmeans(data, k):\n    '''Return final labels and cluster centers.'''\n    labels = initialize_clusters(data, k)\n    centers = []\n    \n    while True:\n        # 1. Update centers based on current labels\n        # 2. Create new_labels by assigning each point to the nearest center\n        # 3. Check for convergence (if new_labels == labels: break)\n        # 4. labels = new_labels\n        # YOUR CODE HERE\n        break # remove this\n        \n    return labels, centers"),
