cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\nExplain how you would write a `MinimaxPlayer` that never loses at Tic-Tac-Toe. What does the algorithm do conceptually?\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\nMinimax generates a **Game Tree** of every possible future move. At the bottom of the tree, it scores wins as +1, losses as -1, and ties as 0.\nIt then percolates these scores back up the tree. When it is X's turn, X chooses the move that *maximizes* the score. When it is O's turn, O chooses the move that *minimizes* the score.\nBecause the search space of Tic-Tac-Toe is tiny ($< 362,880$ nodes), Minimax can see the end of the game from turn 1 and play perfectly.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Algorithms 18 (Euler Estimation)")
